data.title: Atestat de Competente Profesionale La Limba Engleza - Rudyard Kipling
data.meta_description: Ate Stat - Free download as Word Doc (.doc), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Rudyard Kipling was an English author born in 1865 in Bombay, India. He is best known for his works of fiction set in India like The Jungle Book and Kim, as well as his poems. He received the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1907 at a young age. The document provides details about Kipling's childhood in India and England, his early career working for newspapers in India, and his rise to fame as a writer of stories and poems celebrating British imperialism. It discusses his upbringing, education, and first jobs which helped inspire his literary works.
